title: Nicki Minaj pregnant? Fans freak out over rapper's epic baby bump reveal
text:
INSTAGRAM WAIT, WHAT? Nicki stunned fans with this bump reveal 
The Super Bass rapper has sent her fans into a frenzy by revealing a massive baby bump on Instagram. 
Just after her friend Beyoncé announced she was expecting twins via an OTT Instagram shoot, Miss Minaj brought her own pregnancy showcase to the social media site. 
In a picture shared with her 73.2 million followers, the 34-year-old showed off a massive bump in a sheer black vest. 
INSTAGRAM CONFUSING: Nicki had a flat tummy just before the bump showcase Nicki Minaj puts on a curvy display Tuesday, 13th December 2016 Nicki Minaj is one of the hottest acts to enter the global music scene. Here's a look at the fascinating woman behind the voices, characters and crazy costumes. 1 / 109 “I was gonna wait to share the news but...” Nicki Minaj 
The racy lingerie also exposed a whole lot of sideboob, but full focus was on Nicki's blossoming belly. 
Nicki captioned the pic: "ATBIMS. y'all so childish OMGSKLKZFCBNUF - I was gonna wait to share the news but…" 
The photograph sent her fans into meltdown, mainly because nobody could agree whether the pic was legit or not. 
Many comments read: "Congratulations", while others asked: "Who's the father?" 
INSTAGRAM TRENDSETTER: Beyoncé's pregnancy announcement has sparked a wave of copycats Bump It Up: The Most Popular Pregnant Celeb Photos Thursday, 2nd February 2017 See a list of celebrities who posed naked and pregnant for magazines and more scandalous nude celeb baby bump photos. 1 / 20 
Some people tagged Nicki's ex Meek Mill and rumoured love interest Drake in the comment sections. 
However, many others insisted the photo was faked, with a lot of comments pointing out that the pic was Photoshopped. 
Considering Nicki previously posted a picture of herself rocking a washboard-flat tummy in a high-cut swimsuit, we're gonna go with that theory. 
Plus, the "ATBIMS" reference in the caption means "all these bitches is my son" – a line that features in multiple Nicki songs. 
GETTY SPECULATION: Meek Mill previously hinted he was having a baby with Nicki Related videos
